commit.message:
Smoke tests training batch (#147)

Refactor the training batch analyzer:

* Update documentation style
* Separate main call that parses args and "library" call that executes the work. Today we don't test the library portion of the tool in detail (fine), but we could break it out in the future with a unit test file if useful.
* Shorten flag names

Add first set of smoke tests for the tools. These tests don't test the tool functionality in detail. They ensure the tool runs according to the expected usage and should break if some fundamental formats or assumptions are violated in the future. This gives us light protection against tool rot as the code base and logging evolves over time.

commit.message:
Action inversion checker (#141)

The action inversion checker identifies when a policy used to identify a preferred action for a state and then stopped. It will be part of our tool set in debugging why/when the policies starts diverging badly after converging.

This PR submits a standalone utility tied to current bridge building problems.

Future PRs will:

1. Integrate the action inversion checker into the builder_trainer
2. Log the ActionInversionReports via object logger
3. Create a simple visualization or log browse utility to debug.

This PR also creates a debug directory into which we may move other tools.

commit.message:
Update the training panel to use object logs (#120)

This PR ends the long story arc to migrate the training history logging and viewing to use the new logging infrastructure.

The Training Viewer is now only supported as an offline tool to be run after object logs are written during a bridge_builder.py --debug run. The viewer code is simplified to largely reflect training_panel.py. The previous training_panel.py, training_history.py and training_history_test.py are no longer needed in the new system.

commit.message:
Object Log Reader Functions (#119)

Create a shared file for object log reader functions and add TrainingHistoryDatabase as a object log reading tool.

The TrainingHistoryDatabase provides query access above training history and state object logs. The current use-case is to support the training viewer, which will be migrated to use the TrainingHistoryDatabase in the next PR.
